sections.english:
Thus have I heard: On one occasion the Blessed One was dwelling in Rājagaha, on Vulture Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had departed. Then, when the night was far advanced, Brahmā Sahampati, resplendent in his beauty, illuminating the entire Vulture Peak Mountain, approached the Blessed One. Having approached and saluted the Blessed One, he stood to one side. Standing to one side, Brahmā Sahampati, concerning Devadatta, uttered this verse in the presence of the Blessed One:

"Indeed, fruit destroys the plantain, fruit destroys the bamboo, fruit destroys the reed;
Honor destroys the evil person, just as a fetus destroys a she-mule."
